cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a novel positioning solution used in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives the mean square error (MSE) of the maximum likelihood (ML) estimator, which is a common topic in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance of a positioning system, which can be considered a control system. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses a system that involves multiple agents (wireless sensors) working together to achieve a common goal (positioning). 
5. cs.PE (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance of the ML estimator in two different configurations, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
